ONNX model files are protobuf pb files, you can load them with any protobuf library in any language. In fact, the ONNX checker is implemented in C++. e.g. you can do this to print the number of inputs in a model:

```c++
#include "onnx/onnx_pb.h"
#include "onnx/proto_utils.h"

...
std::unique_ptr<ModelProto> model(new ModelProto());
onnx::ParseProtoFromBytes(model.get(), bytes, nbytes);

std::cout << model->graph().input().size() << std::endl;
...
```
